-- Former Philadelphia Flyers Defeat Rangers Alumni 3-1 in NHL Winter Classic
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-01-01T05:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-01/former-philadelphia-flyers-defeat-new-york-rangers-alumni-3-1.html
Philadelphia Flyers alumni defeated a
team of former New York Rangers players 3-1 as a warm-up to the
 National Hockey League ’s outdoor 2012 Winter Classic.  John LeClair, Shjon Podein and Mark Howe each scored
yesterday for the Flyers, while Glen Anderson got the only goal
for the Rangers on an ice rink set up at Citizens Bank Park, the
home of  Major League Baseball ’s Philadelphia Phillies.  Eric Lindros, Bobby Clarke and Bernie Parent were among the
former Flyers who skated yesterday. Mark Messier, Brian Leetch,
Adam Graves and Stephane Matteau joined alumni from the Rangers.  The NHL’s Flyers and Rangers clash in the Winter Classic
tomorrow at 1 p.m.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
